<paragraph base="F32570028" id="IFRS09_5.1.2"><paranum>5.1.2</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 9"/><data name="paranum" value="5.1.2"/></prolog><body><p id="IFRS09_P0288">When an entity uses settlement date accounting for an asset that is subsequently measured at <xref base="F32570588" href="IFRS09_APPA.dita#IFRS09_APPA/IFRS09_P0666">amortised cost<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0013"/></ph></xref>, the asset is recognised initially at its fair value on the trade date (see <xref base="F41732303" href="IFRS09_B3.1.3.dita#IFRS09_B3.1.3" id="IFRS09_X0424">paragraphs B3.1.3&#x2013;B3.1.6</xref>). </p></body></paragraph>